&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for two rotational Assistant Patient Pathway Administrators within Specialist Surgery within the NOTSSCaN Division.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 2-3 Link Grade – Assistant Patient Pathway Administrators&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specialist Surgery&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fu&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ll time - 37.5 hours&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holders will provide a professional, comprehensive and effective administration support service to the Patient Pathway Administrators and the wider medical teams assisting in any administrational duties that may be required to ensure a full administration service is provided within the various services of the Directorate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a rotational role which will enable the successful candidate to rotate within the different Departments within Specialist Surgery, giving them a wide range of knowledge of the division.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are self-motivated and eager to learn, we would encourage you to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hollie.charlett@ouh.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
